request.description:
This endpoint makes an HTTP POST request to create a new file in a GitLab project repository. The request is sent to https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/8300723/repository/files/ccd%2Fnewfile%20md?branch=master. The request body is of type raw and includes the keys "content" and "commit_message".

### Request Body
- `content` (text): The content of the new file.
- `commit_message` (text): The commit message for adding the new file.

The response to the request has a status code of 201 and a content type of application/json. The response body includes the keys "file_path" and "branch".

### Response Body
- `file_path`: The path of the newly created file.
- `branch`: The branch in which the file was created.

To upload a file to the actual repo you need to use the [/projects/:id/repository/files/:file_path](https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/api/repository_files.html#create-new-file-in-repository) endpoint. To upload an **image** specifically, you'll need to: - Set the `encoding` parameter to `base64` - Convert your image to base64 - Remove the `data:image/png;base64,` part at the beginning - Set the `content` parameter to the remaining part of the base64
